<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1368,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,1368,1393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[333,485,1369,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis box="[333,485,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows diagnostic features of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1068,1369,1393]" genus="Cilissa" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[990,1068,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Cilissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: scutum smooth between punctures, male S 
<number box="[296,310,1405,1429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
with apicolateral structure pointed and male gonostylus shorter than gonocoxite. Apicolateral structure of S 
<number box="[249,263,1441,1465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
is pointed like in 
<taxonomicName box="[469,630,1441,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="budashkini">
<emphasis box="[469,630,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. budashkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[645,762,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoana">
<emphasis box="[645,762,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. ezoana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[819,943,1441,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[819,943,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and gonostylus is curved like in 
<taxonomicName box="[1318,1435,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoana">
<emphasis box="[1318,1435,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. ezoana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,321,1477,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[198,321,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two morphological features of 
<taxonomicName box="[687,836,1477,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis box="[687,836,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">M. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique within the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1240,1477,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Melitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1240,1477,1501]" name="Malta" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis box="[1159,1240,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Melitta</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
: reddish legs and the large size (&gt; 
<quantity box="[329,406,1513,1537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="14.0">14mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1368,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,340,1549,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Description</emphasis>
Ƥ (
<figureCitation box="[387,458,1549,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[442,458,1549,1573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[482,628,1549,1573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[645,750,1549,1573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3199999999999998" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="13.2">13.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[764,834,1549,1573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Head.</emphasis>
L = 
<quantity box="[895,986,1549,1573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. W = 
<quantity box="[1060,1152,1549,1573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
. Cuticle black and shiny except mandible, labrum and ventral face of antenna that are reddish-brown. Galea brown, sculptured and mat. Glossa twice as long as paraglossa. Clypeus apically smooth and shiny, sparsely punctate on the anterior part. Face and vertex densely punctate (d&gt;i). Pilosity whitish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[729,855,1657,1681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[916,1005,1657,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
. W (between tegulae) = 
<quantity box="[1279,1368,1657,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Cuticle black, densely punctate (d&gt;i), smooth between punctures. Propodeal triangle mat, sculptured and carinated. Pilosity dense and whitish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[457,513,1729,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Legs</emphasis>
. Cuticle reddish except coxa 
<number box="[844,887,1729,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
, trochanter 
<number box="[1020,1062,1729,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
and F 
<number box="[1137,1148,1729,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
. Pilosity of F 
<number box="[1300,1339,1729,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
whitish, other parts of the legs reddish or yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[659,729,1765,1789]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[713,729,1765,1789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Scopa reddish to whitish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1061,1136,1765,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Wings</emphasis>
. Hyaline. Tegulae yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1801,1825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Metasoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[336,425,1801,1825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
. W = 
<quantity box="[493,582,1801,1825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
. Cuticle black and shiny, densely punctate (d=i), except apical part of sterna reddish. Pygidial plate flat. Disc of T 
<number box="[577,619,1837,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
with erected black hairs anteriorly and reddish apical hairs. Disc of T 
<number box="[1422,1436,1837,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="4.0">4</number>
with reddish hairs. T 
<number box="[386,427,1873,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with wide apical white hair band, half as wide as tergum width. Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae reddish. Disc of sterna with reddish and whitish hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1368,2005]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,535]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<number box="[201,222,1945,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[237,306,1945,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[290,306,1945,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[327,471,1945,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[485,568,1945,1969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[578,649,1945,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Head.</emphasis>
L = 
<quantity box="[703,771,1945,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
. W = 
<quantity box="[838,927,1945,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. Cuticle and pilosity like female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1303,1429,1945,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[199,281,1981,2005]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5mm</quantity>
. W (between tegulae) = 
<quantity box="[557,626,1981,2005]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
. Cuticle and pilosity like female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1005,1061,1981,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Legs</emphasis>
. Cuticle and pilosity like female, except Tb 
<number box="[271,312,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
brownish (
<figureCitation box="[441,509,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[494,509,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[542,617,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Wings</emphasis>
. Like female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[783,907,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Metasoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[971,1061,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
. W = 
<quantity box="[1131,1221,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
. Disc of terga with whitish hairs. Terga with continous apical hair bands. Prepygidial fimbria yellowish to reddish. S 
<number box="[1241,1256,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="6.0">6</number>
with dense reddish apical pilosity. S 
<number box="[389,403,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="7.0">7</number>
with apicolateral plate and apicolateral fringes of long simple hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1237,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1222,1237,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
d). S 
<number box="[1289,1303,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
with nearly hairless disc, apical plate triangular shaped. Genitalia with gonostylus shorter than gonobase (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1269,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1241,1264]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,193,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[207,1379,193,1220]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Melitta magnifica sp. nov. a. Female in dorsal view (scale = 1.6 mm); b. Male in dorsal view (scale = 1.5 mm); c. Genitalia male in dorsal view (scale = 0.3 mm); d. Sterna 7 – 8 in ventral view (scale = 0.4 mm); e. Female in lateral view (scale = 1.6 mm); f. Male in lateral view (scale = 1.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281353/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1253,1269,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c).
</paragraph>
